The 23-year-old, who has previously been a victim of online attacks, said he had received "at least 70 racial slurs" following United's penalty shootout loss to Villarreal in Gdansk on WednesdayUnited, who lost 11-10 on penalties, later tweeted to say their players had been subjected to "disgraceful racist abuse"Last month English football, along with other sporting bodies, united for a four-day social media boycott to urge the companies to take a stronger stance over racial abuse